<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3706] On node crash (RS+DN), the replication of blocks can up latency</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3706</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HDFS is kinda dumb regards rereplication in that if it notices missing replicas, its crass in the way it goes about making redress; there is no facility for limiting the rate of rereplication (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1195&quot; title=&quot;Offer rate limits for replicating data &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HDFS-1195&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HDFS-1195&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).  We&apos;ve seen the case where hdfs is rereplicating at such a rate after DN crash, it fills the network hampering data serving.  This issue is about noting this prob. and helping out/keeping an eye on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1195&quot; title=&quot;Offer rate limits for replicating data &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HDFS-1195&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HDFS-1195&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
